abstract: >-
  Multi-seed empirical study (v2) of GRPO post-training at sub-3B scale on a
  single-GPU LoRA constraint. Compares four arms across three random seeds on
  AMC-23, MATH-500, AIME-2024, and 10-language MGSM. Three orthogonal findings:
  (i) the language-consistency reward arm (A3) achieves the highest mean AIME
  maj@8 with +4.4pp over base, robust across seeds; (ii) vanilla English GRPO
  exhibits sigma=11.3pp seed variance on AMC-23, confirming single-seed claims
  unreliable at this scale; (iii) all training arms ≈ base on 10-language MGSM,
  indicating no cross-lingual transfer. A4 constant-bias ablation partially
  refutes a pure reward-magnitude mechanism interpretation. Source code and
  manuscript prepared with AI assistance (Anthropic Claude via Claude Code
  CLI); all empirical results independently verified. See README and
  VERIFICATION.md for full AI-assistance disclosure.
